description:
The Alex Jones Show

Wednesday January 07, 2009.

Alex talks with attorney Eric Plumlee about cell phone surveillance, retired CIA officer turned political activist Ray McGovern.  And Barry Cooper, a former drug interdiction police officer who has produced the DVD, Never Get Busted Again joins for an extended interview.  Alex also discusses the issues of the day and takes your calls.

Hour-1: News and rants

Hour-2: Eric Plumlee on cell phone surveillance.

Hour-3: Rants on police brutality and executions!  Then Ray McGovern joins for a quick visit.

Hour-4: Barry Cooper in studio.

Hour-5: Barry Cooper in studio.
